## 🔬 About Me
Prof. Dr. M. Tofazzal Islam is an internationally acclaimed biotechnologist and academic. He is the Founder Director of the Institute of Biotechnology and Genetic Engineering (IBGE) at GAU, Bangladesh. Dr. Islam is globally recognized for his pioneering leadership in applying rapid phylogenomics and open science to track the origin and cause of the devastating 2016 wheat blast epidemic in Bangladesh in just weeks. His research primarily explores plant-microbe interactions, crop genomics, genome editing (CRISPR-Cas9), and natural biological solutions to secure agricultural yields and promote sustainable food production.

