## 🧪 Current Research Focus
### Wheat Blast Genomics & Surveillance (Active)
**Role:** Lead Investigator | **Funding:** Ministry of Science and Technology, Bangladesh & international collaborators  
Using genome sequencing, transcriptomics, and CRISPR-Cas9 genome editing to understand the pathogen biology of Magnaporthe oryzae Triticum lineage. Currently breeding blast-resistant wheat varieties and designing rapid CRISPR-based molecular diagnostic kits.

### Discovery of Biocontrol Agents & Rhizosphere Ecology (Active)
**Role:** Principal Investigator | **Funding:** Bangladesh Academy of Sciences & USDA  
Isolating and identifying beneficial endophytic bacteria from marine soils, extreme environments, and wild plants. Analyzing secondary metabolites (e.g., cyclic lipopeptides) that disrupt fungal membranes, offering an organic alternative to chemical fungicides.

### Genome Editing for Salinity and Drought Resistance in Rice (Completed)
**Role:** Co-Investigator | **Funding:** Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation  
Mutagenesis of specific transcription factors in local rice cultivars using CRISPR-Cas9 ribonucleoprotein delivery, showing elevated resilience to coastal soil salinity in field-simulated trials.

