## 🏫 Teaching & Courses
* **Advanced Crop Genomics & Proteomics** (BTC-605) - *Graduate Level*  
  An intensive course focusing on genome sequencing architectures, sequence alignments, genomic annotations, transcriptomics, and mass spectrometry analysis for agricultural improvement.
  
* **Gene Editing & CRISPR-Cas Technology** (BTC-620) - *Postgraduate Level*  
  Covers the mechanics of Cas proteins, single-guide RNA designs, repair templates, off-target detection, and hands-on molecular assembly for editing rice and wheat genomes.
  
* **Introduction to Biotechnology & Biosafety** (BTC-301) - *Undergraduate Level*  
  Undergraduate foundational course covering tissue culture, recombinant DNA history, monoclonal antibodies, and the regulatory frameworks governing genetically modified organisms (GMOs) in Bangladesh.
  

